FlexIn Dance AI
Project Description

FlexIn Dance AI is a computer vision-based platform designed for automated dance training and choreography generation. The system utilizes pose estimation to provide real-time feedback, allowing users to learn professional routines by synchronizing their movements with a digital reference.
Key Features

    Pose Correction System: Real-time analysis of skeletal data using MediaPipe. The system visualizes the user's skeleton and highlights deviations in posture or limb position (Red/Green indicators).

    Split-Screen Interaction: Simultaneous display of a professional reference and the user's camera feed for intuitive "karaoke-style" learning.

    AI Choreography Generation: Processing music tracks and user prompts to generate suggested dance sequences.

    Beat Synchronization: Latency-aware tracking to ensure the user stays in rhythm with the musical composition.

Technical Specifications

    Language: Python 3.12

    Frameworks: OpenCV, MediaPipe (Skeletal Tracking), FastAPI

    Environment: Developed on Ubuntu Linux